As of Monday morning, South Berwick and Ogunquit had the most snow with 4.5 inches and 4.4 inches, respectively, according to the weather service. Falmouth and Gorham topped the Cumberland County charts by Monday morning with 4 inches of snow measured there.

About 3.5 inches of snow was measured in the Portland area Monday morning, while the Lewiston-Auburn area measured at just over an inch.

