Speed limits were reduced to 45 miles per hour along all 109 miles of the Maine Turnpike and along I-295 on Monday morning as flurries continued, but the reduction was lifted by 11 a.m.

The weather resulted in multiple motor vehicle crashes over the long weekend, [including a fatal one in Falmouth](https://www.pressherald.com/2026/01/18/fatal-car-crash-reported-in-falmouth-amidst-snowy-weather/) on Saturday and another that [brought down power lines in Alfred](https://www.pressherald.com/2026/01/19/alfred-crash-involving-plow-knocks-down-power-lines/) on Monday morning.

A number of southern and coastal Maine towns issued parking bans over the weekend, including Bath, Brunswick, Cape Elizabeth, Old Orchard Beach, Saco, Sanford, Scarborough, Topsham and Westbrook.

